Compatibility List
=================
Adapter Support:

D-Link DGE-550T Gigabit Ethernet Adapter.
D-Link DGE-550SX Gigabit Ethernet Adapter.
D-Link DL2000-based Gigabit Ethernet Adapter.


The driver support Linux kernel 2.4.7 later. We had tested it
on the environments below.

 . Red Hat v6.2 (update kernel to 2.4.7)
 . Red Hat v7.0 (update kernel to 2.4.7)
 . Red Hat v7.1 (kernel 2.4.7)
 . Red Hat v7.2 (kernel 2.4.7-10)


Quick Install
=============
Install linux driver as following command:

1. make all
2. insmod dl2k.ko
3. ifconfig eth0 up 10.xxx.xxx.xxx netmask 255.0.0.0
		    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\	    ^^^^^^^^\
				    IP		     NETMASK
Now eth0 should active, you can test it by "ping" or get more information by
"ifconfig". If tested ok, continue the next step.

4. cp dl2k.ko /lib/modules/`uname -r`/kernel/drivers/net
5. Add the following line to /etc/modprobe.d/dl2k.conf:
	alias eth0 dl2k
6. Run depmod to updated module indexes.
7. Run "netconfig" or "netconf" to create configuration script ifcfg-eth0
   located at /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts or create i